    "body": "@kevinsawicki Hi, I tried `webContents.capturePage`, but it can only capture the \"visible\" part of the page. If the height of your `html` node is larger than the BrowserWindow (or when there's a scroll bar), the overflow part is not included in the captured image. Is there any way to capture the whole page?\n\n(tested in macOS 10.12, electron 1.0.2)\n"
